description:
This would have come out better if I had used the Newtonian, but I had the refractor up and this target was well-positioned, so I did it with the refractor. Even with a decent amount of data, I found it very hard to keep the noise down while preserving structure - and there is a lot of interesting structure in this one. 

Also of note is Asteroid 189 Phthia, which can be seen to the center-right of the image. I first thought it was a cosmic ray, but it couldn't find it any of my subs, so I looked more closely and found movement over the 3-hour period I did the RGB field. You can find an animation of it here: https://www.astrobin.com/332490/
imaging_telescopes: Explore Scientific 80mm Carbon Fiber Air-Spaced Triplet ED APO Refractor
title: Abell 31 / Sh2-290 / PK 219+31.1 (Asteroid 189 Phthia)
